The paper describes a deep convolutional neural network approach for hyperspectral image classification, which involves exploiting both spatial and spectral features. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep learning techniques and the focus on classification suggest that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. Finally, the use of hyperspectral imaging data suggests that the paper may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
